## Current Site Analysis

| Aspect | Current State | Issues |
|--------|--------------|--------|
| **Homepage** | "Welcome to AllThingsCambridge" + 4 level cards (Checkpoint, O Level, IGCSE, A Level) + features section | Feels like a dashboard, not a landing page. Lacks hero impact and polish |
| **Sidebar** | Always-visible left sidebar with Learning Resources, Community, Information sections | Takes up too much space; feels like an admin panel rather than a study platform |
| **Header** | Logo + dark mode toggle + Log In / Sign Up | Clean but minimal |
| **Color Scheme** | Deep teal (#0d9488) primary, light gray background | Decent but could be more vibrant. Lacks visual hierarchy |
| **Flashcards** | Tab exists but shows "No Flashcards Available" — no actual flashcard UI built | Needs full implementation from scratch |
| **Navigation** | Level → Subject → Resource Type (tabbed) | Functional but lacks breadcrumbs and topic-level drilling |

## Benchmark (SaveMyExams) Key Design Patterns

### Flashcard Design ⭐
- **Large centered card** with rounded corners + subtle shadow
- **Stack effect** — visual representation of cards behind
- **3D flip animation** on click (Front/Back labels)
- **Progress indicator**: "1/68" counter + thin progress bar
- **Learning tracker**: "Still learning" (red) and "Know" (green) pill buttons
- **Topic header** with breadcrumb navigation above
- **"Download" button** for offline access

### Navigation
- **Two-tier sidebar**: Primary nav (left) + Topic nav (center-left, collapsible with chapters/subtopics)
- **Clean breadcrumbs**: GCSE / Biology / AQA / Flashcards / Cell Structure
- **"Hide menu" toggle** for distraction-free study mode

### Visual Polish
- Modern sans-serif typography (Inter-like)
- White & light gray backgrounds with blue (#0055FF) accents
- Clean spacing and card-based layouts
- Trust signals and CTA buttons

---

## What Needs to Change (Scope)

### 🔴 Must Do (Client Requirements)
1. **Better Homepage UI** — More visually impactful hero section, better visual hierarchy
2. **Flashcard Design** — Match the benchmark's card-based study mode with flip animations, progress tracking, and learning/known categorization

### 🟡 Should Do (Recommended Improvements)
3. **Breadcrumb navigation** — for deep content like Level > Subject > Topic > Flashcard
4. **Collapsible sidebar** — study mode / distraction-free reading
5. **Topic-level navigation** for flashcards (like SaveMyExams' chapter/subtopic sidebar)
6. **Progress tracking UI** on flashcard pages

### 🟢 Nice to Have
7. **Micro-animations** — smooth transitions, hover effects
8. **Dark mode polish** — make it feel premium
9. **Mobile responsiveness** improvements

---

## What to Keep (Don't Change)
- ✅ Overall app structure (sidebar + main content area)
- ✅ Level system (Checkpoint, O Level, IGCSE, A Level)
- ✅ Resource tabs (Notes, Past Papers, Topical Questions, Flashcards)
- ✅ Auth system (login/signup in header)
- ✅ Community section (Forums, Blog, Testimonials)
- ✅ Dark mode toggle
